HEADWORD: Zeppelin
<hw>Zep`pe*lin"</hw> <pr>(ts⟦ecr⟧p`p⟦etil⟧*l⟦emac⟧"; <it>Angl.</it>
z⟦ecr⟧p"p⟦esl⟧*l⟦icr⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A dirigible balloon of
the rigid type, consisting of a cylindrical trussed and covered frame
supported by internal gas cells, and provided with means of propulsion
and control. It was first successfully used by <person>Ferdinand Count
von Zeppelin</person>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

